Triggered only if one of the selected fi: Triggered only if one of the selected fields changes. If unselected, it means that it will be triggered when any field changes. When record is added or deleted, any field is considered to have been changed.
Based on date field of collection: Based on date field of collection
This node contains branches, deleting wi: This node contains branches, deleting will also be preformed to them, are you sure?
Fields that are not assigned a value wil: Fields that are not assigned a value will be set to the default value, and those that do not have a default value are set to null.
Trigger in executed workflow cannot be m: Trigger in executed workflow cannot be modified
Node in executed workflow cannot be modi: Node in executed workflow cannot be modified
The result of this node has been referen: The result of this node has been referenced by other nodes ({{nodes}}), please remove the usage before deleting.
Event triggers when submitted a workflow: Event triggers when submitted a workflow bound form action.
Use a collection to match form data.
Counting, summing, finding maximum, mini: Counting, summing, finding maximum, minimum, and average values for multiple records of a collection or associated data of a record.
Delay a period of time and then continue: Delay a period of time and then continue or exit the process. Can be used to set wait or timeout times in parallel branches.
Calculate an expression based on a calcu: Calculate an expression based on a calculation engine and obtain a value as the result. Variables in the upstream nodes can be used in the expression. The expression is dynamic one from an expression collections.
Select the dynamic expression queried fr: Select the dynamic expression queried from the upstream node. You need to query it from an expression collection.
An expression for calculation in each ro: An expression for calculation in each rows
By using a loop node, you can perform th: By using a loop node, you can perform the same operation on multiple sets of data. The source of these sets can be either multiple records from a query node or multiple associated records of a single record. Loop node can also be used for iterating a certain number of times or for looping through each character in a string. However, excessive looping may cause performance issues, so use with caution.
A single number will be treated as a loo: A single number will be treated as a loop count, a single string will be treated as an array of characters, and other non-array values will be converted to arrays. The loop node ends when the loop count is reached, or when the array loop is completed. You can also add condition nodes to the loop to terminate it.
Could be used for manually submitting da: Could be used for manually submitting data, and determine whether to continue or exit. Workflow will generate a todo item for assigned user when it reaches a manual node, and continue processing after user submits the form.
Values preset in this form will override: Values preset in this form will override user submitted ones when continue or reject.
Run multiple branch processes in paralle: Run multiple branch processes in parallel.
Continue after any branch succeeded, or: Continue after any branch succeeded, or exit after any branch failed.
Send HTTP request to a URL. You can use: Send HTTP request to a URL. You can use the variables in the upstream nodes as request headers, parameters and request body.
\"Content-Type\" only support \"applicat: "Content-Type" only support "application/json", and no need to specify
Ignore failed request and continue workf: Ignore failed request and continue workflow
Execute a SQL statement in database: Execute a SQL statement in database
Usage of SQL query result is not support: Usage of SQL query result is not supported yet.
